# JSON Data Formats

## Canonical JSONL Data Files (defaults/data/)

Line-delimited JSON (`.jsonl`). Two entry types:

### Node
```json
{"entitytype":"node","id":"<uuid>","nodetype":"npc","properties":{"name":"Hari Seldon","role":"psychohistorian","skills":["Psychohistory-5"],"tags":["Founder"]}}
```

Fields:
- `entitytype`: always `"node"`
- `id`: UUID v4 string — generated at conversion time, stable across re-imports
- `nodetype`: must match a schema type (`npc`, `location`, `faction`, etc.)
- `properties`: typed JSON object. Values match the property types declared in the schema:
  - `string`/`text`/`number` fields → JSON string or number
  - `array` fields → native JSON array (e.g. `["a", "b"]`)
  - `boolean` fields → JSON boolean

### Edge
```json
{"entitytype":"edge","from":"Hari Seldon","to":"Trantor","edgeType":"lived_on"}
```

Fields:
- `entitytype`: always `"edge"`
- `from`: source node name (resolved against the name index)
- `to`: target node name
- `edgeType`: string-based relationship type

### Supported Node Types
npc, player_character, location, faction, quest, artifact, currency, skills, temporal, setting_reference, system_reference, transportation, inventory

