## Schema Files (defaults/schemas/)

Named `*.schema.json`. Define object types and validation rules.

```json
{
  "name": "add_npc",
  "description": "Add a new NPC to the knowledge graph",
  "properties": {
    "name": { "type": "string", "required": true },
    "skills": { "type": "array", "description": "Skills the NPC possesses" },
    "currentLocation": {
      "type": "string",
      "relationship": { "edgeType": "located_in" }
    }
  }
}
```

### Property types
`string`, `text`, `number`, `boolean`, `array`, `object`, `reference`, `enum`

### Validation rules
`min_length`, `max_length`, `min_value`, `max_value`, `pattern` (regex), `allowed_values`, `required`

### Naming convention
Files use `add_` prefix in `name` field (MCP tool convention). `SchemaIngestion` strips the prefix — `add_npc` becomes `npc` internally. Schemas are saved under the `"imported_schemas"` namespace; the UI loads both `"default"` (built-in hardcoded types) and `"imported_schemas"` at startup.

