## Sample Data

`defaults/data/memory.jsonl`: ~220 nodes + ~312 edges from Isaac Asimov's Foundation universe. Canonical JSONL format. Used by the CLI demo and integration tests.

`defaults/data/memory.json`: original MemoryMesh export — legacy format, kept as a conversion reference. Use `memory.jsonl` for all imports.

```bash
# Count nodes by type
jq -c 'select(.entitytype == "node") | .nodetype' defaults/data/memory.jsonl | sort | uniq -c

# Inspect a specific type
jq -c 'select(.entitytype == "node" and .nodetype == "npc")' defaults/data/memory.jsonl | head -2

# Find edges
jq -c 'select(.entitytype == "edge")' defaults/data/memory.jsonl | head
```
